The paper focuses on decentralized control strategies for a team of robots to track a target, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of self-triggered communication and observability criteria for partner selection suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MA). The paper also mentions evaluating the approaches through simulations, which could indicate a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for testing and analysis.
